
Overview of noun comb

The noun comb has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) comb -- (a flat device with narrow pointed teeth on one edge; disentangles or arranges hair)
2. (1) comb, cockscomb, coxcomb -- (the fleshy red crest on the head of the domestic fowl and other gallinaceous birds)
3. comb -- (any of several tools for straightening fibers)
4. comb -- (ciliated comb-like swimming plate of a ctenophore)
5. comb, combing -- (the act of drawing a comb through hair; "his hair needed a comb")

Overview of verb comb

The verb comb has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) comb -- (straighten with a comb; "comb your hair")
2. (1) comb, ransack -- (search thoroughly; "They combed the area for the missing child")
